<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1689,2038]" pageId="0" pageNumber="273">
This genus can be distinguished from other genera of 
<taxonomicName box="[780,889,1689,1714]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Thripinae">Thripinae</taxonomicName>
by the long abdominal segment X with almost parallel margins and the polygonal reticulation on the metanotum and abdominal tergites and sternites.
</paragraph>
